      "id": "PopularPost324808",
      "post_content": "\"*It's good to know that WotC is finally embracing the fact that life gain isn't as good as initially thought.*\"  \n-- HairlessThoctar  \n  \n*Pretty* sure they knew about this during Kamigawa cycle already.  \nCompare it with [Sunbeam Spellbomb](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sunbeam Spellbomb) or [Nourish](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Nourish) for example, which came one cycle earlier.  \n  \nIt's just one of their needlessly overcosted cards they feel like printing every now and then.  \nThis could easily have been cheaper, an instant, or even both. Compare it to [Reviving Dose](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Reviving Dose).  \n  \nLife gain cantrips can be pretty useful actually, especially at instant speed.  \n[Renewed Faith](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Renewed Faith) for example has great versatility.  \n  \nI'd still play **Dosan's Oldest Chant** over [Blessed Wine](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Blessed Wine), [Bargain](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Bargain) and [Rejuvenate](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Rejuvenate), though.  \n  \nThat said, it sursprisingly seems to be the only green life gain cantrip so far.",
      "posted_by": "Mode",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost324808\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_post\">\"<i>It's good to know that WotC is finally embracing the fact that life gain isn't as good as initially thought.</i>\"<br/>-- HairlessThoctar<br/><br/><i>Pretty</i> sure they knew about this during Kamigawa cycle already.<br/>Compare it with <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Sunbeam Spellbomb\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sunbeam Spellbomb\">Sunbeam Spellbomb</a> or <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Nourish\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Nourish\">Nourish</a> for example, which came one cycle earlier.<br/><br/>It's just one of their needlessly overcosted cards they feel like printing every now and then.<br/>This could easily have been cheaper, an instant, or even both. Compare it to <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Reviving Dose\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Reviving Dose\">Reviving Dose</a>.<br/><br/>Life gain cantrips can be pretty useful actually, especially at instant speed.<br/><a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Renewed Faith\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Renewed Faith\">Renewed Faith</a> for example has great versatility.<br/><br/>I'd still play <b>Dosan's Oldest Chant</b> over <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Blessed Wine\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Blessed Wine\">Blessed Wine</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Bargain\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Bargain\">Bargain</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Rejuvenate\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Rejuvenate\">Rejuvenate</a>, though.<br/><br/>That said, it sursprisingly seems to be the only green life gain cantrip so far.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a hr