      "id": "PopularPost93791",
      "post_content": "Yeah this card should have a better rating. This /was/ part of the response to lifegain being rubbish. They've just taken it further with certain cards. But this goes fine in several casual decks and is ok in limited. Compare with something like [nourish](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=nourish) - it seems worse, but generally the cost isn't the problem with these cards. I mean rarely is being able to get nourish off quicker going to make the difference.",
